<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1754,2033]" pageId="24" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,356,1863,1889]" pageId="24" pageNumber="63">Morphology:</emphasis>
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3400666305" collectionCode="SZN" pageId="24" pageNumber="63" specimenCode="POR207" specimenCount="1">
As explained above, the 
<typeStatus box="[654,702,1863,1889]" pageId="24" pageNumber="63">type</typeStatus>
material (
<collectionCode box="[822,877,1863,1889]" pageId="24" pageNumber="63">SZN</collectionCode>
<specimenCode box="[887,986,1863,1889]" collectionCode="POR" country="Italy" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14383" name="Università degli Studi di Napoli Federico II" pageId="24" pageNumber="63" type="Herbarium">POR207</specimenCode>
) could not be analysed, and additional samples were not available or could not be located. According to the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Sara, M." box="[1153,1271,1899,1926]" pageId="24" pageNumber="63" pagination="421 - 472" refId="ref17462" refString="Sara, M. (1960) Poriferi del litorale dell'isola d'lschia e loro ripartizione ambienti. Pubblicazioni della Stazione zoologica di Napoli, 31 (3), 421 - 472." type="journal article" year="1960">Sarà 1960</bibRefCitation>
), the specimen has an ellipsoidal shape and apical osculum without fringe of trichoxeas. No data about the aquiferous system is provided, and the lack of illustrations of the skeletal or histological organisations prevented any inferences from being made
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1437]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,150,176]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Anatomy:</emphasis>
The cortical skeleton is formed by triactines and giant tetractines, which point the apical actines to the middle of the sponge body (
<bibRefCitation author="Sara, M." box="[513,633,187,214]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="421 - 472" refId="ref17462" refString="Sara, M. (1960) Poriferi del litorale dell'isola d'lschia e loro ripartizione ambienti. Pubblicazioni della Stazione zoologica di Napoli, 31 (3), 421 - 472." type="journal article" year="1960">Sarà 1960</bibRefCitation>
). Microdiactines are present along the whole skeleton, but 
<bibRefCitation author="Sara, M." box="[1304,1436,187,214]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="421 - 472" refId="ref17462" refString="Sara, M. (1960) Poriferi del litorale dell'isola d'lschia e loro ripartizione ambienti. Pubblicazioni della Stazione zoologica di Napoli, 31 (3), 421 - 472." type="journal article" year="1960">Sarà (1960)</bibRefCitation>
emphasised they are more abundant at the atrial skeleton, which is also formed by small and particular tetractines (see remarks below).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1437]" box="[199,737,294,322]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,297,294,320]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Spicules</emphasis>
(according to the original description):
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1437]" box="[199,1082,331,357]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Cortical tetractines: Giant, actines have similar length (700–1200/70–120 μm).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1437]" box="[199,1063,366,393]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Cortical triactines: Smaller than the cortical tetractines (170–350/15–35 μm).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1437]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Atrial tetractines (see remarks below): They have a particular (harpoon) shape. Apical (70–80/ 7–9 μm) and unpaired (55–70 μm) actines are considerably longer than the paired ones (20–35 μm).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1437]" box="[199,673,475,501]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Microdiactines: Lanceolate (60–70/4 μm).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1437]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,511,537]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Remarks:</emphasis>
Due to the small size of the 
<typeStatus box="[647,695,511,537]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">type</typeStatus>
specimen (&lt;
<quantity box="[851,902,511,537]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" unit="cm" value="1.0">1cm</quantity>
), it could not be loaned, and microscope slides could not be prepared by the current staff of the Stazione Zoologica Anton Dohrn di Napoli (Andrea Travaglini, personal communication). Nevertheless, based only on the original description, we figured out that (1) important characters typical of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haeckel" authorityYear="1870" box="[394,540,619,645]" class="Calcarea" family="Amphoriscidae" genus="Amphoriscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[394,540,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Amphoriscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were not reported along the description of this species, such as the syconoid aquiferous system and the inarticulate skeleton formed by the apical actines of the cortical tetractines and the unpaired actine of the subatrial spicules; and (2) the shape of the small atrial tetractines, of which “la forma è molto caratteristica” (
<bibRefCitation author="Sara, M." box="[325,447,727,754]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="421 - 472" refId="ref17462" refString="Sara, M. (1960) Poriferi del litorale dell'isola d'lschia e loro ripartizione ambienti. Pubblicazioni della Stazione zoologica di Napoli, 31 (3), 421 - 472." type="journal article" year="1960">Sarà 1960</bibRefCitation>
), suggesting that they are pugioles. These spicules correspond to small harpoon—(or dagger-) shaped spicules present in the order 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borojevic, Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet" authorityYear="2000" box="[659,746,763,789]" class="Calcarea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="order">Baerida</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Borojevic, R. &amp; Boury-Esnault, N. &amp; Manuel, M. &amp; Vacelet, J." box="[760,1003,763,789]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="1958" refId="ref15986" refString="Borojevic, R., Boury-Esnault, N., Manuel, M. &amp; Vacelet, J. (2002) Order Leucosolenida Hartman, 1958. In: Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; Van Soest, R. W. M. (Eds.), Systema Porifera: a guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2. Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, New York, Boston, Dordrecht, London and Moscow, pp. 1157 - 1184. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 1 - 4615 - 0747 - 5 _ 120" type="book chapter" year="2002">
Borojevic 
<emphasis box="[880,929,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 2002
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Alvizu, A. &amp; Eilertsen, M. H. &amp; Xavier, J. R. &amp; Rapp, H. T." box="[1012,1217,763,789]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="279 - 290" refId="ref15624" refString="Alvizu, A., Eilertsen, M. H., Xavier, J. R. &amp; Rapp, H. T. (2018) Increased taxon sampling provides new insights into the phylogeny and evolution of the subclass Calcaronea (Porifera, Calcarea). Organisms Diversity &amp; Evolution, 18 (3), 279 - 290. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13127 - 018 - 0368 - 4" type="journal article" year="2018">
Alvizu 
<emphasis box="[1095,1145,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Alvizu, A. &amp; Xavier, J. R. &amp; Rapp, H. T." box="[1228,1289,763,789]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="201 - 251" refId="ref15704" refString="Alvizu, A., Xavier, J. R. &amp; Rapp, H. T. (2019) Description of new chiactine-bearing sponges provides insights into the higher classification of Calcaronea (Porifera: Calcarea). Zootaxa, 4615 (2), 201 - 251. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4615.2.1" type="journal article" year="2019">2019</bibRefCitation>
). Besides the presence of pugioles, the description provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sara, M." box="[719,852,799,826]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="421 - 472" refId="ref17462" refString="Sara, M. (1960) Poriferi del litorale dell'isola d'lschia e loro ripartizione ambienti. Pubblicazioni della Stazione zoologica di Napoli, 31 (3), 421 - 472." type="journal article" year="1960">Sarà (1960)</bibRefCitation>
contains other characters found in the definition of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borojevic, Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet" authorityYear="2000" box="[151,243,835,861]" class="Calcarea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="order">Baerida</taxonomicName>
: the presence of cortical large and giant spicules (triactines and tetractines, respectively, in the case of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sara" authorityYear="1960" class="Calcarea" family="Amphoriscidae" genus="Amphoriscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="dohrni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">A. dohrni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the presence of microdiactines abundant in the atrial skeleton (although it is not clear if they are more abundant than the atrial pugioles). Therefore, based on these features, there is no support for keeping the species inside the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haeckel" authorityYear="1870" box="[339,485,943,969]" class="Calcarea" family="Amphoriscidae" genus="Amphoriscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[339,485,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Amphoriscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and we propose to transfer it to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borojevic, Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet" authorityYear="2000" box="[854,945,943,969]" class="Calcarea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="order">Baerida</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1437]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">
According to Van Soest 
<emphasis box="[474,524,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. (2021), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borojevic, Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet" authorityYear="2000" box="[627,714,979,1005]" class="Calcarea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="order">Baerida</taxonomicName>
is formed by four families: 
<taxonomicName authority="Borojevic, Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet, 2000" authorityName="Borojevic, Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet" authorityYear="2000" class="Calcarea" family="Baeriidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">
Baeriidae 
<bibRefCitation author="Borojevic, R. &amp; Boury-Esnault, N. &amp; Vacelet, J." pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="203 - 263" refId="ref15941" refString="Borojevic, R., Boury-Esnault, N. &amp; Vacelet, J. (2000) A revision of the supraspecific classification of the subclass Calcaronea (Porifera, class Calcarea). Zoosystema, 22 (2), 203 - 263." type="journal article" year="2000">Borojevic, Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Borojevic, 1979" authorityName="Borojevic" authorityYear="1979" box="[350,698,1015,1041]" class="Calcarea" family="Petrobionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Petrobionidae Borojevic, 1979</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Borojevic, Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet, 2000" authorityName="Borojevic, Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet" authorityYear="2000" box="[710,1383,1015,1041]" class="Calcarea" family="Trichogypsiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">
Trichogypsiidae 
<bibRefCitation author="Borojevic, R. &amp; Boury-Esnault, N. &amp; Vacelet, J." box="[900,1383,1015,1041]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="203 - 263" refId="ref15941" refString="Borojevic, R., Boury-Esnault, N. &amp; Vacelet, J. (2000) A revision of the supraspecific classification of the subclass Calcaronea (Porifera, class Calcarea). Zoosystema, 22 (2), 203 - 263." type="journal article" year="2000">Borojevic, Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Vacelet, 1967" authorityName="Vacelet" authorityYear="1967" box="[151,516,1051,1077]" class="Calcarea" family="Lepidoleuconidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Lepidoleuconidae Vacelet, 1967</taxonomicName>
. Among the families mentioned above, only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borojevic, Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet" authorityYear="2000" box="[1026,1133,1051,1077]" class="Calcarea" family="Baeriidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Baeriidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borojevic" authorityYear="1979" box="[1190,1346,1051,1077]" class="Calcarea" family="Petrobionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Petrobionidae</taxonomicName>
include pugioles in their composition (
<bibRefCitation author="Borojevic, R. &amp; Boury-Esnault, N. &amp; Manuel, M. &amp; Vacelet, J." box="[507,760,1087,1113]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="1958" refId="ref15986" refString="Borojevic, R., Boury-Esnault, N., Manuel, M. &amp; Vacelet, J. (2002) Order Leucosolenida Hartman, 1958. In: Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; Van Soest, R. W. M. (Eds.), Systema Porifera: a guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2. Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, New York, Boston, Dordrecht, London and Moscow, pp. 1157 - 1184. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 1 - 4615 - 0747 - 5 _ 120" type="book chapter" year="2002">
Borojevic 
<emphasis box="[630,683,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 2002
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Alvizu, A. &amp; Xavier, J. R. &amp; Rapp, H. T." box="[773,991,1087,1113]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="201 - 251" refId="ref15704" refString="Alvizu, A., Xavier, J. R. &amp; Rapp, H. T. (2019) Description of new chiactine-bearing sponges provides insights into the higher classification of Calcaronea (Porifera: Calcarea). Zootaxa, 4615 (2), 201 - 251. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4615.2.1" type="journal article" year="2019">
Alvizu 
<emphasis box="[860,913,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borojevic" authorityYear="1979" box="[1013,1169,1087,1113]" class="Calcarea" family="Petrobionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Petrobionidae</taxonomicName>
has a basal calcareous skeleton of calcite. This family is monotypic, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Vacelet &amp; Levi, 1958" authorityName="Vacelet &amp; Levi" authorityYear="1958" box="[720,1224,1122,1149]" class="Calcarea" family="Petrobionidae" genus="Petrobiona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="massiliana">
<emphasis box="[720,974,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Petrobiona massiliana</emphasis>
Vacelet &amp; Lévi, 1958
</taxonomicName>
does not resemble “ 
<emphasis box="[164,181,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">A</emphasis>
”. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sara" authorityYear="1960" box="[207,282,1159,1185]" class="Calcarea" family="Amphoriscidae" genus="Amphoriscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="dohrni">
<emphasis box="[207,282,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">dohrni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in which the basal skeleton is absent (
<bibRefCitation author="Borojevic, R. &amp; Boury-Esnault, N. &amp; Manuel, M. &amp; Vacelet, J." box="[715,958,1159,1185]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="1958" refId="ref15986" refString="Borojevic, R., Boury-Esnault, N., Manuel, M. &amp; Vacelet, J. (2002) Order Leucosolenida Hartman, 1958. In: Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; Van Soest, R. W. M. (Eds.), Systema Porifera: a guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2. Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, New York, Boston, Dordrecht, London and Moscow, pp. 1157 - 1184. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 1 - 4615 - 0747 - 5 _ 120" type="book chapter" year="2002">
Borojevic 
<emphasis box="[834,883,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 2002
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borojevic, Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet" authorityYear="2000" box="[976,1083,1159,1185]" class="Calcarea" family="Baeriidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Baeriidae</taxonomicName>
includes four genera: 
<taxonomicName authority="Grant, 1833" authorityName="Grant" authorityYear="1833" class="Calcarea" family="Baeriidae" genus="Leuconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1332,1436,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Leuconia</emphasis>
Grant, 1833
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Polejaeff, 1883" authorityName="Polejaeff" authorityYear="1883" box="[307,602,1195,1221]" class="Calcarea" family="Baeriidae" genus="Eilhardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[307,413,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Eilhardia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Polejaeff, N." box="[425,602,1195,1221]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref17300" refString="Polejaeff, N. (1883) Report on the Calcarea dredged by H. M. S. ' Challenger', during the years 1873 - 1876. Report on the Scientific Results of the Voyage of H. M. S. ' Challenger', 1873 - 1876. Zoology, 8 (2), 1 - 76." type="journal article" year="1883">Poléjaeff, 1883</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirk, 1895" authorityName="Kirk" authorityYear="1895" box="[618,865,1194,1221]" class="Calcarea" family="Baeriidae" genus="Lamontia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[618,725,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Lamontia</emphasis>
Kirk, 1895
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Dendy &amp; Row, 1913" authorityName="Dendy &amp; Row" authorityYear="1913" box="[931,1313,1195,1221]" class="Calcarea" family="Baeriidae" genus="Leucopsila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[931,1054,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Leucopsila</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dendy, A. &amp; Row, R. W. H." box="[1066,1313,1195,1221]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="704 - 813" refId="ref16638" refString="Dendy, A. &amp; Row, R. W. H. (1913) The Classification and Phylogeny of the Calcareous Sponges, with a reference list of all the described species, systematically arranged. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 3, 704 - 813. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1913. tb 06152. x" type="journal article" year="1913">Dendy &amp; Row, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grant" authorityYear="1833" box="[210,314,1231,1256]" class="Calcarea" family="Baeriidae" genus="Leuconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[210,314,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Leuconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and possibly 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirk" authorityYear="1895" box="[475,582,1231,1256]" class="Calcarea" family="Baeriidae" genus="Lamontia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[475,582,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Lamontia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are pugiole-bearing genera. The latter is characterised by having diactines perforating the cortex and microdiactines throughout the choanoskeleton, characters that were not reported for “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haeckel" authorityYear="1870" box="[164,310,1303,1329]" class="Calcarea" family="Amphoriscidae" genus="Amphoriscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[164,310,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Amphoriscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sara" authorityYear="1960" box="[330,405,1303,1329]" class="Calcarea" family="Amphoriscidae" genus="Amphoriscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="dohrni">
<emphasis box="[330,405,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">dohrni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sara, M." box="[419,537,1303,1329]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="421 - 472" refId="ref17462" refString="Sara, M. (1960) Poriferi del litorale dell'isola d'lschia e loro ripartizione ambienti. Pubblicazioni della Stazione zoologica di Napoli, 31 (3), 421 - 472." type="journal article" year="1960">Sarà 1960</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Borojevic, R. &amp; Boury-Esnault, N. &amp; Manuel, M. &amp; Vacelet, J." box="[549,792,1303,1329]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="1958" refId="ref15986" refString="Borojevic, R., Boury-Esnault, N., Manuel, M. &amp; Vacelet, J. (2002) Order Leucosolenida Hartman, 1958. In: Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; Van Soest, R. W. M. (Eds.), Systema Porifera: a guide to the classification of sponges. Vol. 2. Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, New York, Boston, Dordrecht, London and Moscow, pp. 1157 - 1184. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 1 - 4615 - 0747 - 5 _ 120" type="book chapter" year="2002">
Borojevic 
<emphasis box="[667,717,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 2002
</bibRefCitation>
). Since this species does have atrial pugioles, we decided to allocate it within 
<emphasis box="[384,498,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Leuconia¸</emphasis>
despite the absence of sagittal triactines in the atrium. We therefore highlight the need for a taxonomic revision of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grant" authorityYear="1833" box="[524,628,1375,1400]" class="Calcarea" family="Baeriidae" genus="Leuconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[524,628,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">Leuconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the entire order 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borojevic, Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet" authorityYear="2000" box="[862,952,1375,1401]" class="Calcarea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Baerida" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" phylum="Porifera" rank="order">Baerida</taxonomicName>
, echoing recent suggestions from 
<bibRefCitation author="Alvizu, A. &amp; Eilertsen, M. H. &amp; Xavier, J. R. &amp; Rapp, H. T." pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="279 - 290" refId="ref15624" refString="Alvizu, A., Eilertsen, M. H., Xavier, J. R. &amp; Rapp, H. T. (2018) Increased taxon sampling provides new insights into the phylogeny and evolution of the subclass Calcaronea (Porifera, Calcarea). Organisms Diversity &amp; Evolution, 18 (3), 279 - 290. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13127 - 018 - 0368 - 4" type="journal article" year="2018">
Alvizu 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. (2018
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Alvizu, A. &amp; Xavier, J. R. &amp; Rapp, H. T." box="[266,327,1411,1437]" pageId="25" pageNumber="64" pagination="201 - 251" refId="ref15704" refString="Alvizu, A., Xavier, J. R. &amp; Rapp, H. T. (2019) Description of new chiactine-bearing sponges provides insights into the higher classification of Calcaronea (Porifera: Calcarea). Zootaxa, 4615 (2), 201 - 251. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4615.2.1" type="journal article" year="2019">2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
